         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Perhaps you &amp; Bentham have not the first edit of Linné's syst. nat (of 1735). ¶  I find at p. 9, that he has  ¶ Lens ¶  as a genus, though (of course) the name only. Still it is entitled to be ment...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.11.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller 1871-81, f. 345.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Correspondent identified by the reference to Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), and to Bentham. Dated to late 1881 by the reference to figure of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Micraira">Micraira</name>, </seg>and to B82.13.08 being in press.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Perhaps you &amp; Bentham have not the first edit of Linné's syst. nat (of 1735).<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Linnaeus (1735).</p>
               </note> I find at p. 9, that he has <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Lens">Lens</name>
               </seg> as a genus, though (of course) the name only. Still it is entitled to be mentioned thus far as generic authority<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 1, p. 525 attribute <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Lens">Lens</name>
                     </seg>to Grenier and Godron (1848-56), vol. 1, p. 476.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have quoted the first edition in my census of Austral plant-genera, now in type,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B82.13.08.</p>
               </note> wherever it had priority. "<name key="Sassafras">Sassafras</name>" occurs also at p. 9.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was greatly pleased with the figure of <name key="Micraira">Micraira</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Micraira">Micraira</name> subulifolia</seg> was illustrated in J. Hooker (1867-89), vol. 14, t. 1361, p. 43, issued in October 1881.</p>
               </note> I subscribe to all your &amp; Bentham's publications, Bot. Mag., Genera, icones, &amp;c &amp;c for my private library.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lens">Lens</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Micraira">Micraira</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sassafras">Sassafras</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
